</item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/111019830165351945</link><description>Neural signature of flexible coding in prefrontal cortex&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.2200400119" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;doi.org/10.1073/pnas.220040011&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fediscience.org/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111019830241472373</guid><pubDate>Wed, 06 Sep 2023 19:22:50 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Earl K. Miller</title><link>https://fediscience.org/@ekmiller/111019836132153786</link><description>Dynamic and stable population coding of attentional instructions coexist in the prefrontal cortex&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.2202564119" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;doi.org/10.1073/pnas.220256411&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class="mention hashtag" href="https://fediscience.org/tags/neuroscience" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;#&lt;span&gt;neuroscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111019836355924062</guid><pubDate>Wed, 06 Sep 2023 19:24:21 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Jesse Louis-Rosenberg</title><link>https://mathstodon.xyz/@nervous_jesse/111019490568770784</link><description>The discovery of an aperiodic monotile was greeted with much fanfare. It was not the Spectre tile, but the "hat" shown on the left. Of course we were also excited and almost immediately received requests to make some. However, some mathematicians were slightly dissatisfied, because the tiling actually required reflections or flipping over tiles. Therefore in some ways it was actually two shapes not one. This is not simply mathematical frippery, it is actually key to fabricating a puzzle. Because if you print a pattern on one side of the puzzle, it won‚Äôt work. The tiles must be flipped when assembling, so sometimes you would end up with the image side down. So we were delighted when the same team announced the Spectre on May 28, an aperiodic monotile that does not require reflections.&lt;a href="https://cs.uwaterloo.ca/~csk/hat/" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;cs.uwaterloo.ca/~csk/hat/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/019/490/690/906/233/original/cb289d34d09623a3.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/019/490/690/906/233/original/cb289d34d09623a3.png" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/019/490/800/668/261/original/e31a28f1e14fb5a7.png"&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.mastodon.social/cache/media_attachments/files/111/019/490/800/668/261/original/e31a28f1e14fb5a7.png" alt="Mastodon image" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">111020050485768917</guid><pubDate>Wed, 06 Sep 2023 20:18:52 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>European Commission</title><link>https://social.network.europa.eu/@EU_Commission/111017787528870307</link><description>Alphabet, Amazon, Apple, ByteDance, Meta, MicrosoftThese are the first 6 companies designated as ‚Äògatekeepers' under the Digital Markets Act.They have 6 months to ensure their core platform services comply with our rules, including:‚úî Allowing users to unsubscribe and remove pre-installed services&lt;br/&gt;‚úî Allowing the download of alterna